HEADWORD: Hypersthene
<hw>Hy"per*sthene</hw> <pr>(h⟦imac⟧"p⟦etil⟧r*sth⟦emac⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>"ype`r</grk> over + <grk>sqe`nos</grk>
strength: cf. F. <ets>hyperst⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>An orthorhombic mineral of the pyroxene group, of a grayish or
greenish black color, often with a peculiar bronzelike luster (schiller)
on the cleavage surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

